decLesConfigTable.name: decLesConfigTable
decLesConfigTable.description: A table describing all the LES components which this managed device supports.

decLesConfigEntry.name: decLesConfigEntry
decLesConfigEntry.description: Each row describes one LES component, which might be either a standalone LES or part of a distributed LES.

decLesIndex.name: decLesIndex
decLesIndex.description: A unique number greater than zero which identifies this table row.

decLesRowStatus.name: decLesRowStatus
decLesRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete LAN Emulation Server components. If this object is writable, it will accept the values 'createAndGo' 'destroy' under suitable conditions. Use decLesAdminStatus to enable and disable service.

decLesAdminStatus.name: decLesAdminStatus
decLesAdminStatus.description: The desired state of this LES component. When a LES is distributed, this object controls the 'local' server component, as opposed to the overall state of the LES. If a BUS is connected to the LES, enabling/disabling either server may affect both of them. Otherwise it is up to the network manager to coordinate the state of the servers.

decLesOperStatus.name: decLesOperStatus
decLesOperStatus.description: The operational state of this LES component. A LES component may not become operational until it has been configured with values for LAN Type Maximum Data Frame Size Control Time-out BUS ATM Address When a LES is in the 'disabling' or 'deleting' state, attempts to set decLesAdminStatus to 'up' will fail.

decLesLastChange.name: decLesLastChange
decLesLastChange.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time that this server last entered its current operational state. If the current state was entered prior to the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

decLesAtmAddress.name: decLesAtmAddress
decLesAtmAddress.description: The ATM address of this LAN Emulation Server, or LAN Emulation Server component. Clients establish Control Direct VCCs to this address to initiate the process of Joining the emulated LAN.

decLesDescription.name: decLesDescription
decLesDescription.description: A human-readable string which can contain anything the network manager wants.

decLesLanName.name: decLesLanName
decLesLanName.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.1.1
decLesLanName.description: The name of this emulated LAN. This can be any string that the network manager would like this LES component to pass out to new clients. This string is not guaranteed to uniquely identify the emulated LAN.

decLesLanType.name: decLesLanType
decLesLanType.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.1.2
decLesLanType.description: The data frame format for this emulated LAN. In an active emulated LAN, this parameter MUST have a consistent value in all of the LES and BUS components serving the emulated LAN. Otherwise various problems may result. The value of this columnar object may only be changed when this LAN Emulation Server has no active clients, and 'decLes[Admin,Oper]Status' are 'down'.

decLesMaxDataFrameSize.name: decLesMaxDataFrameSize
decLesMaxDataFrameSize.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.1.2
decLesMaxDataFrameSize.description: The maximum AAL-5 SDU size for data frames sent over this emulated LAN. This must be one of the standard sizes defined in the LAN Emulation specification. In an active emulated LAN, this parameter MUST have a consistent value in all of the LES and BUS components serving the emulated LAN. Otherwise various problems may result. The value of this columnar object may only be changed when this LAN Emulation Server has no active clients, and 'decLes[Admin,Oper]Status' are 'down'.

decLesAtmAddressOfBUS.name: decLesAtmAddressOfBUS
decLesAtmAddressOfBUS.description: The ATM address of the Broadcast and Unknown Server component associated with this LES component. Unless otherwise stated in product documentation, the value of this columnar object may only be changed when this LAN Emulation Server has no active clients, and 'decLes[Admin,Oper]Status' are 'down'.

decLesControlTimeout.name: decLesControlTimeout
decLesControlTimeout.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.1.2
decLesControlTimeout.description: S4 Control Time-out. Time out period used for timing out most request/response control frame interactions, as specified elsewhere. Once a LE Client establishes a Control Direct VCC to the LE Server, the Join phase must complete within the Join Time-out time. If not, the LE Service SHOULD release any Control VCCs to that LE Client, terminating the Join phase. If a LES is distributed, each of its servers should have the same value for this parameter.

decLesArpResponsePolicy.name: decLesArpResponsePolicy
decLesArpResponsePolicy.description: Lets you fine-tune the performance of an emulated LAN by controlling the distribution of LE_ARP_RESPONSEs. You can choose from one of three policies: unspecified(1) Leave everything up to the implementation. direct(2) The LES sends responses only to the client to which they are directed. This reduces the amount of overhead per response packet, but may result in more LE_ARP traffic. broadcast(3) The LES sends responses to all clients via the Control Direct VCC. This lets clients learn LE_ARP information by eavesdropping, but also increases per-packet overhead.

decLesNarpRequestPolicy.name: decLesNarpRequestPolicy
decLesNarpRequestPolicy.description: Controls whether this LES forwards LE_NARP_REQUESTs.

decLesTopologyChangeMode.name: decLesTopologyChangeMode
decLesTopologyChangeMode.description: The Topology Change mode which this LE Server believes the emulated LAN is in, based upon the Topology Change requests it has seen and/or generated. The value 'true' indicates accelerated aging mode - as opposed to normal aging mode.

decLesLastTcModeChange.name: decLesLastTcModeChange
decLesLastTcModeChange.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time that the object 'decLesTopologyChangeMode' last acquired its current value. If the current value was acquired prior to the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

decLesTopologyChangeTimeout.name: decLesTopologyChangeTimeout
decLesTopologyChangeTimeout.description: Provides a guard against an emulated LAN remaining in accelerated aging mode forever. If an emulated LAN remains in the accelerated aging state for more than 'decLesTopologyChangeTimeout' seconds following the last Topology Request, the LE Server will automatically issue a Topology Request frame to reset all the clients to normal aging mode. This value is measured in seconds, and should be set higher than the normal time between bridge BPDUs.

decLesClientStatesTable.name: decLesClientStatesTable
decLesClientStatesTable.description: A table describing how many clients are in various membership states.

decLesClientStatesEntry.name: decLesClientStatesEntry
decLesClientStatesEntry.description: Each row contains counters for one LES component.

decLesActiveClients.name: decLesActiveClients
decLesActiveClients.description: The number of active clients of this LES component.

decLesActiveProxyClients.name: decLesActiveProxyClients
decLesActiveProxyClients.description: The number of active proxy clients of this LES component.

decLesAwaitingJoinRequest.name: decLesAwaitingJoinRequest
decLesAwaitingJoinRequest.description: The number of Control Direct VCCs on which this LES component is waiting for a Join request.

decLesCtlDistributeInProgress.name: decLesCtlDistributeInProgress
decLesCtlDistributeInProgress.description: The number of clients to which this LES component is currently establishing Control Distribute VCCs.

decLesTerminating.name: decLesTerminating
decLesTerminating.description: The number of clients whose memberships this LES component is in the process of terminating.

decLesClientTable.name: decLesClientTable
decLesClientTable.description: A table listing clients which belong to the emulated LANs that this node serves. This table reflects the actual state of each emulated LAN, as opposed to the way the network manager would like to see LE clients and servers configured. This table contains only local clients - that is, to say, clients connected directly to one of the server components which this agent manages.

decLesClientEntry.name: decLesClientEntry
decLesClientEntry.description: Each entry describes an active LAN Emulation Client, from the perspective of the LES.

decLesClientID.name: decLesClientID
decLesClientID.description: The LEC-ID which the LES handed to the LAN Emulation Client as part of the Join process.

decLesClientAtmAddress.name: decLesClientAtmAddress
decLesClientAtmAddress.description: The primary ATM address of the LAN Emulation Client.

decLesClientIsProxy.name: decLesClientIsProxy
decLesClientIsProxy.description: Indicates whether this client is a proxy client.

decLesClientState.name: decLesClientState
decLesClientState.description: Indicates the status of this LEC from the server's perspective.

decLesClientRowStatus.name: decLesClientRowStatus
decLesClientRowStatus.description: Provides a way to disconnect a LEC from the emulated LAN. When read, this object has the value 'active'. When written, it accepts the value 'destroy'. Because the ability to disconnect clients could lead to denial-of-service attacks, support for this feature is strictly optional.

decLesLecTable.name: decLesLecTable
decLesLecTable.description: A table listing clients which belong to the emulated LANs that this node serves.

decLesLecEntry.name: decLesLecEntry
decLesLecEntry.description: Each entry describes a LAN Emulation Client from the perspective of the LES.

decLesLecAtmAddress.name: decLesLecAtmAddress
decLesLecAtmAddress.description: The primary ATM address of the LAN Emulation Client.

decLesLecID.name: decLesLecID
decLesLecID.description: For an active client, the LEC-ID that the LES handed to the client as part of the Join process. For an inactive client, the value zero.

decLesLecIsProxy.name: decLesLecIsProxy
decLesLecIsProxy.description: Indicates whether this client is a proxy client.

decLesLecState.name: decLesLecState
decLesLecState.description: Indicates the status of this LEC from the server's perspective.

decLesLecRowStatus.name: decLesLecRowStatus
decLesLecRowStatus.description: Provides a way to disconnect a LEC from the emulated LAN. When read, this object has the value 'active'. When written, it only accepts the value 'destroy'. Because the ability to disconnect clients could lead to denial-of-service attacks, support for this feature is strictly optional.

decLesCtlDirectTable.name: decLesCtlDirectTable
decLesCtlDirectTable.description: This optional table identifies Control Direct VCCs at the place where they attach to the LES. In a SVC implementation, the objects in this table will be read-only. In a PVC implementation, this table can be used to tell the LES about the creation or the deletion of Control Direct VCCs.

decLesCtlDirectEntry.name: decLesCtlDirectEntry
decLesCtlDirectEntry.description: Each entry describes the circuits going to one LAN Emulation Client.

decLesControlDirectInterface.name: decLesControlDirectInterface
decLesControlDirectInterface.description: If a Control Direct VCC exists, this object contains the 'ifIndex' of the ATM port which terminates that circuit at the LES. Otherwise, its value is 0.

decLesControlDirectVpi.name: decLesControlDirectVpi
decLesControlDirectVpi.description: If a Control Direct VCC exists, this object contains the VPI of the Control Direct VCC at the point where it connects to the LES. Otherwise, its value is 0.

decLesControlDirectVci.name: decLesControlDirectVci
decLesControlDirectVci.description: If a Control Direct VCC exists, this object contains the VCI of the Control Direct VCC at the point where it connects to the LES. Otherwise, its value is 0.

decLesControlDirectRowStatus.name: decLesControlDirectRowStatus
decLesControlDirectRowStatus.description: Used to create and delete rows in the table.

decLesCtlDistTable.name: decLesCtlDistTable
decLesCtlDistTable.description: This optional table identifies Control Distribute VCCs at the place where they attach to the LES. In a SVC implementation, this table will be read- only. In a PVC implementation, this table can be used to tell the LES about the creation or the deletion of Control Distribute VCCs.

decLesCtlDistEntry.name: decLesCtlDistEntry
decLesCtlDistEntry.description: Each entry describes one Control Distribute VCC.

decLesControlDistInterface.name: decLesControlDistInterface
decLesControlDistInterface.description: The 'ifIndex' of the ATM port which terminates the Control Distribute VCC at the LES.

decLesControlDistVpi.name: decLesControlDistVpi
decLesControlDistVpi.description: The VPI of the Control Distribute VCC at the point where this VCC connects to the LES.

decLesControlDistVci.name: decLesControlDistVci
decLesControlDistVci.description: The VCI of the Control Distribute VCC at the point where this VCC connects to the LES.

decLesControlDistRowStatus.name: decLesControlDistRowStatus
decLesControlDistRowStatus.description: An object provided to satisfy the requirement that all tables have at least one accessible object; in the future, it may also be extended to provide PVC support.

decLesMacAddressTable.name: decLesMacAddressTable
decLesMacAddressTable.description: A table of unicast MAC addresses registered with this host's LES components by their local clients.

decLesMacAddressEntry.name: decLesMacAddressEntry
decLesMacAddressEntry.description: Each entry describes one registered (MAC address, ATM address) pair.

decLesMacAddress.name: decLesMacAddress
decLesMacAddress.description: One of the MAC addresses registered with the LAN Emulation Server 'decLesIndex'.

decLesMacAddressOwner.name: decLesMacAddressOwner
decLesMacAddressOwner.description: The LECID of the client that registered this MAC address.

decLesMacAddressAtmBinding.name: decLesMacAddressAtmBinding
decLesMacAddressAtmBinding.description: The ATM address associated with this MAC address.

decLesRouteDescrTable.name: decLesRouteDescrTable
decLesRouteDescrTable.description: A table of IEEE 802.5 Route Descriptors registered with this host's LES components by their local clients.

decLesRouteDescrEntry.name: decLesRouteDescrEntry
decLesRouteDescrEntry.description: Each table row describes a (Route Descriptor, ATM address) pair registered for a particular client.

decLesRouteDescrSegmentID.name: decLesRouteDescrSegmentID
decLesRouteDescrSegmentID.description: The LAN ID portion of the IEEE 802.5 route descriptor associated with this conceptual row.

decLesRouteDescrBridgeNumber.name: decLesRouteDescrBridgeNumber
decLesRouteDescrBridgeNumber.description: The Bridge Number portion of the IEEE 802.5 route descriptor associated with this conceptual row.

decLesRouteDescrOwner.name: decLesRouteDescrOwner
decLesRouteDescrOwner.description: The LECID of the client that registered this route descriptor.

decLesRouteDescrAtmBinding.name: decLesRouteDescrAtmBinding
decLesRouteDescrAtmBinding.description: The ATM address registered for the IEEE 802.5 route descriptor ('decLesRouteDescrSegmentID', 'decLesRouteDescrBridgeNumber').

decLesTrafficTable.name: decLesTrafficTable
decLesTrafficTable.description: A table of traffic statistics, with one row for each Broadcast and Unknown Server.

decLesTrafficEntry.name: decLesTrafficEntry
decLesTrafficEntry.description: A set of traffic statistics for one BUS component.

decLesControlFramesIn.name: decLesControlFramesIn
decLesControlFramesIn.description: The total number of control frames received by this LES component. This includes invalid frames.

decLesShortFrames.name: decLesShortFrames
decLesShortFrames.description: The number of frames which were discarded because they were too short, and which are not included in any other error count.

decLesUnjoinedClientFrames.name: decLesUnjoinedClientFrames
decLesUnjoinedClientFrames.description: The number of frames which were discarded because a client had not completed the Join process, and which are not included in any other error count.

decLesVersionsNotSupported.name: decLesVersionsNotSupported
decLesVersionsNotSupported.description: The number of frames which were discarded because they specified a version of the LAN Emulation protocol which the server does not support. This count does not include Join frames counted by the MIB object 'decLesJoinVersionsNotSupported'.

decLesInvalidFrames.name: decLesInvalidFrames
decLesInvalidFrames.description: The number of frames which were discarded because of invalid frame formats, and which are not included in any other error count. This counter includes frames with invalid MARKERs and OPCODEs.

decLesReceiveQueueDiscards.name: decLesReceiveQueueDiscards
decLesReceiveQueueDiscards.description: The number of frames discarded due to receive queue overflows, and not included in other discard counts.

decLesMiscDiscards.name: decLesMiscDiscards
decLesMiscDiscards.description: The number of incoming frames which were discarded due to no fault of their own, and which are not included in any other discard count or error count.

decLesCallStatsTable.name: decLesCallStatsTable
decLesCallStatsTable.description: This table holds statistics on virtual circuit/leaf establishment attempts. It contains one row for each LAN Emulation Server, and acts as an extension to 'decLesServicesTable'.

decLesCallStatsEntry.name: decLesCallStatsEntry
decLesCallStatsEntry.description: Each row contains connection statistics for one LAN Emulation Server.

decLesCtlDirectCalls.name: decLesCtlDirectCalls
decLesCtlDirectCalls.description: The total number of Control Direct VCC establishment attempts for this LES component.

decLesCtlDirectFailures.name: decLesCtlDirectFailures
decLesCtlDirectFailures.description: The number of Control Direct establishment attempts for this LES component which were not accepted. This includes failures counted in decLesCtlDirectOutOfResources decLesCtlDirectInvalidInfoElements and any miscellaneous failures.

decLesCtlDirectOutOfResources.name: decLesCtlDirectOutOfResources
decLesCtlDirectOutOfResources.description: The number of Control Direct establishment attempts for this LES component which failed for lack of resources.

decLesCtlDirectInvalidInfoElements.name: decLesCtlDirectInvalidInfoElements
decLesCtlDirectInvalidInfoElements.description: The number of Control Direct establishment attempts for this LES component which failed because required information elements were missing or contained invalid information. The optional Event Log group can help you determine which information elements were invalid or missing.

decLesCtlDistributeCalls.name: decLesCtlDistributeCalls
decLesCtlDistributeCalls.description: The total number of Control Distribute connections which this LES component tried to establish to clients.

decLesCtlDistributeFailures.name: decLesCtlDistributeFailures
decLesCtlDistributeFailures.description: The number of Control Distribute connections which this LES component was unable to establish. This includes failures counted in decLesCtlDistribOutOfResources decLesJoinCtlDistributeRejects and any miscellaneous failures.

decLesCtlDistribOutOfResources.name: decLesCtlDistribOutOfResources
decLesCtlDistribOutOfResources.description: The number of Control Distribute connections which this LES component could not establish due to lack of resources.

decLesJoinTable.name: decLesJoinTable
decLesJoinTable.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.4
decLesJoinTable.description: This table holds statistics on Join attempts. It contains one row for each managed LES component.

decLesJoinEntry.name: decLesJoinEntry
decLesJoinEntry.description: Each row contains Join statistics for one LES.

decLesJoinRequests.name: decLesJoinRequests
decLesJoinRequests.description: The total number of Join requests received by this LES component.

decLesJoinSuccesses.name: decLesJoinSuccesses
decLesJoinSuccesses.description: The number of first-time Join requests accepted by this LES component.

decLesJoinFailures.name: decLesJoinFailures
decLesJoinFailures.description: The number of first-time Join requests rejected by this LES component. This includes requests counted in decLesJoinInvalidParameters decLesJoinDuplicateAtmAddresses decLesJoinDuplicateLanDestinations decLesJoinInvalidAtmAddresses decLesJoinInvalidLanDestinations decLesJoinWrongLanTypes decLesJoinMaxFrameSizesTooSmall decLesJoinInvalidLECIDs decLesJoinCtlDistributeRejects decLesJoinOutOfResources This value does not include failures counted in decLesJoinDuplicates decLesJoinNonDuplicates decLesJoinDiscards decLesJoinTimeouts decLesJoinVersionsNotSupported

decLesJoinDuplicates.name: decLesJoinDuplicates
decLesJoinDuplicates.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.4.2.14
decLesJoinDuplicates.description: The number of duplicate Join requests received by this LES component. Each duplicate Join request is answered with a duplicate Join response. These do not count towards the various 'successful Join' and 'failed Join' statistics.

decLesJoinNonDuplicates.name: decLesJoinNonDuplicates
decLesJoinNonDuplicates.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.4.2.14
decLesJoinNonDuplicates.description: The number of Join requests which were rejected by this LES component because they differed from previous Join requests received over the same Control Direct VCCs. Clients which send such requests are terminated.

decLesJoinDiscards.name: decLesJoinDiscards
decLesJoinDiscards.description: The number of Join requests which were discarded due to no fault of their own, and for which this LES component sent no Join response.

decLesJoinTimeouts.name: decLesJoinTimeouts
decLesJoinTimeouts.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.4.2.2
decLesJoinTimeouts.description: The number of Control Direct VCCs which this LES closed because their callers failed to send Join requests within a reasonable time-out period.

decLesJoinVersionsNotSupported.name: decLesJoinVersionsNotSupported
decLesJoinVersionsNotSupported.description: The number of Join requests which were ignored by this LES component because they specified a version of the LAN Emulation protocol which the server does not support. As per the specification, such requests are not answered with response frames.

decLesJoinInvalidParameters.name: decLesJoinInvalidParameters
decLesJoinInvalidParameters.description: The number of Join requests which were rejected by this LES component due to invalid parameters (such as a non-zero STATUS in the Join request frame).

decLesJoinDuplicateAtmAddresses.name: decLesJoinDuplicateAtmAddresses
decLesJoinDuplicateAtmAddresses.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.4.2.6
decLesJoinDuplicateAtmAddresses.description: The number of Join requests which were rejected by this LES component because they specified a duplicate ATM address.

decLesJoinDuplicateLanDestinations.name: decLesJoinDuplicateLanDestinations
decLesJoinDuplicateLanDestinations.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.4.2.5
decLesJoinDuplicateLanDestinations.description: The number of Join requests which were rejected by this LES component because they specified a duplicate LAN destination.

decLesJoinInvalidAtmAddresses.name: decLesJoinInvalidAtmAddresses
decLesJoinInvalidAtmAddresses.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Sections 4.2, 5.1.1
decLesJoinInvalidAtmAddresses.description: The number of Join requests which were rejected by this LES component because they specified an invalid ATM address, or because the would-be clients violated the rules concerning primary ATM addresses.

decLesJoinInvalidLanDestinations.name: decLesJoinInvalidLanDestinations
decLesJoinInvalidLanDestinations.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.4.2.4
decLesJoinInvalidLanDestinations.description: The number of Join requests which were rejected by this LES component because they specified an illegal LAN destination, such as a multicast or broadcast MAC address.

decLesJoinWrongLanTypes.name: decLesJoinWrongLanTypes
decLesJoinWrongLanTypes.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.4.2.4
decLesJoinWrongLanTypes.description: The number of Join requests which were rejected by this LES component because they specified the wrong LAN Type.

decLesJoinMaxFrameSizesTooSmall.name: decLesJoinMaxFrameSizesTooSmall
decLesJoinMaxFrameSizesTooSmall.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.4.2.4
decLesJoinMaxFrameSizesTooSmall.description: The number of Join requests which were rejected by this LES component because they specified a maximum frame size smaller than the one configured for the emulated LAN.

decLesJoinInvalidLECIDs.name: decLesJoinInvalidLECIDs
decLesJoinInvalidLECIDs.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.4.2.6
decLesJoinInvalidLECIDs.description: The number of Join requests which were rejected by this LES component because they specified a REQUESTER-LECID other than zero.

decLesJoinCtlDistributeRejects.name: decLesJoinCtlDistributeRejects
decLesJoinCtlDistributeRejects.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.4.2.7
decLesJoinCtlDistributeRejects.description: The number of Join requests which were rejected by this LES component because the client failed to accept a Control Distribute VCC connection.

decLesJoinOutOfResources.name: decLesJoinOutOfResources
decLesJoinOutOfResources.description: The number of Join requests which were rejected by this LES component because the LES ran out of resources.

decLesJoinRcvQueueDiscards.name: decLesJoinRcvQueueDiscards
decLesJoinRcvQueueDiscards.description: The number of Join request discards which were due to running out of space in Join receive queues.

decLesJoinLecRcvQueueDiscards.name: decLesJoinLecRcvQueueDiscards
decLesJoinLecRcvQueueDiscards.description: The number of Join request discards which were due to running out of space in per-LEC receive queues.

decLesJoinResourceDiscards.name: decLesJoinResourceDiscards
decLesJoinResourceDiscards.description: The number of Join request discards which were due to the server running out of other resources.

decLesRegisterTable.name: decLesRegisterTable
decLesRegisterTable.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Chapter 6
decLesRegisterTable.description: This table holds statistics on Registration attempts. It contains one row for each managed LES component.

decLesRegisterEntry.name: decLesRegisterEntry
decLesRegisterEntry.description: Each row contains registration statistics for one LES.

decLesRegisterRequests.name: decLesRegisterRequests
decLesRegisterRequests.description: The total number of Register requests received by this LAN Emulation Server component.

decLesRegisterSuccesses.name: decLesRegisterSuccesses
decLesRegisterSuccesses.description: The total number of valid registration requests received by this LAN Emulation Server component.

decLesRegisterFailures.name: decLesRegisterFailures
decLesRegisterFailures.description: The total number of invalid registration requests received by this LAN Emulation Server component.

decLesRegisterDiscards.name: decLesRegisterDiscards
decLesRegisterDiscards.description: The number of Register requests which were discarded due to no fault of their own, and for which this LES component sent no Register response.

decLesUnregisterRequests.name: decLesUnregisterRequests
decLesUnregisterRequests.description: The total number of Unregister requests received by this LAN Emulation Server component.

decLesUnregisterSuccesses.name: decLesUnregisterSuccesses
decLesUnregisterSuccesses.description: The total number of valid unregister requests received by this LAN Emulation Server component.

decLesUnregisterFailures.name: decLesUnregisterFailures
decLesUnregisterFailures.description: The total number of invalid unregister requests received by this LAN Emulation Server component.

decLesUnregisterDiscards.name: decLesUnregisterDiscards
decLesUnregisterDiscards.description: The number of Unregister requests which were discarded due to no fault of their own, and for which this LES component sent no Unregister response.

decLesRegDuplicateAtmAddresses.name: decLesRegDuplicateAtmAddresses
decLesRegDuplicateAtmAddresses.description: The number of Register requests that failed because they specified an ATM address already registered to another client.

decLesRegDuplicateLanDestinations.name: decLesRegDuplicateLanDestinations
decLesRegDuplicateLanDestinations.description: The number of Register requests that failed because they specified a LAN Destination already registered to another client.

decLesRegInvalidAtmAddresses.name: decLesRegInvalidAtmAddresses
decLesRegInvalidAtmAddresses.description: The number of Register requests that failed because they contained an invalid ATM address.

decLesRegInvalidLanDestinations.name: decLesRegInvalidLanDestinations
decLesRegInvalidLanDestinations.description: The number of Register requests that failed because they specified an invalid LAN Destination - such as a broadcast or multicast MAC address.

decLesRegInvalidLECIDs.name: decLesRegInvalidLECIDs
decLesRegInvalidLECIDs.description: The number of Register requests that failed because they contained an invalid LEC ID.

decLesRegOutOfResources.name: decLesRegOutOfResources
decLesRegOutOfResources.description: The number of Register requests that failed because the server ran out of resources.

decLesRegRcvQueueDiscards.name: decLesRegRcvQueueDiscards
decLesRegRcvQueueDiscards.description: The number of Register requests which were discarded by this LES component because one of its receive queues was full.

decLesRegLecRcvQueueDiscards.name: decLesRegLecRcvQueueDiscards
decLesRegLecRcvQueueDiscards.description: The number of Register requests which were discarded by this LES component because one of its per-LEC receive queues was full.

decLesRegResourceDiscards.name: decLesRegResourceDiscards
decLesRegResourceDiscards.description: The number of Register requests which were discarded by this LES component because the server ran out of resources.

decLesUnRegInvalidLanDestinations.name: decLesUnRegInvalidLanDestinations
decLesUnRegInvalidLanDestinations.description: The number of Unregister requests that failed because they specified an invalid LAN Destination - such as a broadcast or multicast MAC address.

decLesUnRegInvalidLECIDs.name: decLesUnRegInvalidLECIDs
decLesUnRegInvalidLECIDs.description: The number of Unregister requests that failed because they contained an invalid LEC ID.

decLesUnRegRcvQueueDiscards.name: decLesUnRegRcvQueueDiscards
decLesUnRegRcvQueueDiscards.description: The number of Unregister requests which were discarded by this LES component because one of its receive queues was full.

decLesUnRegLecRcvQueueDiscards.name: decLesUnRegLecRcvQueueDiscards
decLesUnRegLecRcvQueueDiscards.description: The number of Unregister requests which were discarded by this LES component because one of its per-LEC receive queues was full.

decLesUnRegResourceDiscards.name: decLesUnRegResourceDiscards
decLesUnRegResourceDiscards.description: The number of Unregister requests which were discarded by this LES component because the server ran out of resources.

decLesRegAlreadyRegistered.name: decLesRegAlreadyRegistered
decLesRegAlreadyRegistered.description: The number of successful Register requests which had no effect, because the address pairs they specified were already registered to the requesting clients.

decLesUnRegNoSuchLanDestinations.name: decLesUnRegNoSuchLanDestinations
decLesUnRegNoSuchLanDestinations.description: The number of successful Unregister requests which had no effect, because the LAN Destinations that they specified were already unregistered.

decLesUnRegNoSuchAddressPairs.name: decLesUnRegNoSuchAddressPairs
decLesUnRegNoSuchAddressPairs.description: The number of successful Unregister requests which had no effect, because the ATM addresses that they specified did not match the registered ones.

decLesUnRegOwnedByOthers.name: decLesUnRegOwnedByOthers
decLesUnRegOwnedByOthers.description: The number of successful Unregister requests which had no effect, because they attempted to unregister LAN Destinations belonging to other clients.

decLesArpTable.name: decLesArpTable
decLesArpTable.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Chapter 7
decLesArpTable.description: This table holds statistics on LE_ARP_REQUESTs and related LAN Emulation control frames. It contains one row for each managed LES component.

decLesArpEntry.name: decLesArpEntry
decLesArpEntry.description: Each row contains LE-ARP statistics for one LES.

decLesArpRequestsAnswered.name: decLesArpRequestsAnswered
decLesArpRequestsAnswered.description: The number of LE_ARP_REQUESTs which this LES component has answered directly with a Success code.

decLesArpRequestsForwarded.name: decLesArpRequestsForwarded
decLesArpRequestsForwarded.description: The number of LE_ARP_REQUESTs which this LES component has forwarded to clients or other server components.

decLesArpRequestsRejected.name: decLesArpRequestsRejected
decLesArpRequestsRejected.description: The number of LE_ARP_REQUESTs which this LES component has rejected. This includes frames counted in decLesArpReqInvalidAtmAddresses decLesArpReqInvalidLanDestinations decLesArpReqInvalidLECIDs

decLesArpRequestsDiscarded.name: decLesArpRequestsDiscarded
decLesArpRequestsDiscarded.description: The number of LE_ARP_REQUESTs which this LES component has discarded, due to no fault of their own.

decLesArpResponsesForwarded.name: decLesArpResponsesForwarded
decLesArpResponsesForwarded.description: The number of LE_ARP_RESPONSEs which this LES component has forwarded to one or more clients. This count does not include any LE_ARP_RESPONSE which is counted in 'decLesArpRequestsAnswered'.

decLesArpResponsesRejected.name: decLesArpResponsesRejected
decLesArpResponsesRejected.description: The number of LE_ARP_RESPONSEs which this LES component has discarded due to errors. This includes frames counted in decLesArpRespInvalidLECIDs

decLesArpResponsesDiscarded.name: decLesArpResponsesDiscarded
decLesArpResponsesDiscarded.description: The number of LE_ARP_RESPONSEs which this LES component has discarded due to no fault of their own.

decLesNarpRequestsForwarded.name: decLesNarpRequestsForwarded
decLesNarpRequestsForwarded.description: The number of LE_NARP_REQUESTs which this LES component has forwarded to clients.

decLesNarpRequestsFiltered.name: decLesNarpRequestsFiltered
decLesNarpRequestsFiltered.description: The number of LE_NARP_REQUESTs which this LES has filtered (discarded) to enforce management policy. See 'decLesNarpRequestPolicy'.

decLesNarpRequestsRejected.name: decLesNarpRequestsRejected
decLesNarpRequestsRejected.description: The number of LE_NARP_REQUESTs which this LES component has rejected. This includes frames counted in decLesNarpReqInvalidAtmAddresses decLesNarpReqInvalidLanDestinations decLesNarpReqInvalidLECIDs

decLesNarpRequestsDiscarded.description: The number of LE_NARP_REQUESTs which this LES has discarded through no fault of their own, and which are not counted in decLesNarpRequestsFiltered.

decLesTopologyRequestsForwarded.name: decLesTopologyRequestsForwarded

decLesTopologyRequestsRejected.name: decLesTopologyRequestsRejected

decLesTopologyRequestsDiscarded.name: decLesTopologyRequestsDiscarded
decLesTopologyRequestsDiscarded.description: The number of LE_TOPOLOGY_REQUESTs which this LES component has discarded due to no fault of their own.

decLesTopologyRequestGenFailures.name: decLesTopologyRequestGenFailures
decLesTopologyRequestGenFailures.description: The number of LE_TOPOLOGY_REQUESTs which this LES component has tried, but failed, to generate.

decLesArpReqInvalidAtmAddresses.name: decLesArpReqInvalidAtmAddresses
decLesArpReqInvalidAtmAddresses.description: The number of LE_ARP_REQUESTs which were rejected because their ATM addresses were in unrecognizable formats.

decLesArpReqInvalidLanDestinations.description: The number of LE_ARP_REQUESTs which were rejected because they specified invalid LAN Destinations - such as multicast MAC addresses.

decLesArpReqInvalidLECIDs.name: decLesArpReqInvalidLECIDs
decLesArpReqInvalidLECIDs.description: The number of LE_ARP_REQUESTs that were discarded because they contained an invalid LEC ID.

decLesArpReqReceiveQueueDiscards.description: The number of LE_ARP requests which were discarded by this LES component because one of its receive queues was full.

decLesNarpReqInvalidAtmAddresses.name: decLesNarpReqInvalidAtmAddresses
decLesNarpReqInvalidAtmAddresses.description: The number of LE_NARP_REQUESTs which were rejected because their ATM addresses were in unrecognizable formats.

decLesNarpReqInvalidLanDestinations.name: decLesNarpReqInvalidLanDestinations
decLesNarpReqInvalidLanDestinations.description: The number of LE_NARP_REQUESTs that were rejected because they specified invalid LAN Destinations - such as multicast MAC addresses.

decLesNarpReqInvalidLECIDs.name: decLesNarpReqInvalidLECIDs
decLesNarpReqInvalidLECIDs.description: The number of LE_NARP_REQUESTs that were rejected because they contained an invalid LEC ID.

decLesNarpReqReceiveQueueDiscards.name: decLesNarpReqReceiveQueueDiscards
decLesNarpReqReceiveQueueDiscards.description: The number of LE_NARP requests which were discarded by this LES component because one of its receive queues was full.

decLesNarpReqResourceDiscards.name: decLesNarpReqResourceDiscards
decLesNarpReqResourceDiscards.description: The number of LE_NARP requests which were discarded by this LES component because the server ran out of resources.

decLesTopoReqReceiveQueueDiscards.description: The number of LE_TOPOLOGY requests which were discarded by this LES component because one of its receive queues was full.

decLesTopoReqResourceDiscards.name: decLesTopoReqResourceDiscards
decLesTopoReqResourceDiscards.description: The number of LE_TOPOLOGY requests which were discarded by this LES component because the server ran out of resources.

decLesFlushEntry.description: Each row contains Flush statistics for one LES.

decLesEventLogTable.name: decLesEventLogTable
decLesEventLogTable.description: A table of event log entries for the emulated LANs that this node serves.

decLesEventLogEntry.name: decLesEventLogEntry
decLesEventLogEntry.description: An entry describing a significant event.

decLesEventIndex.name: decLesEventIndex
decLesEventIndex.description: A unique number greater than zero which identifies this table row.

decLesEventType.description: The event which triggered this log entry. joinFailed(1) - A client tried to join one of the LANs this host serves, but the attempt failed. registrationFailed(2) - A client was not able to register a new LAN Destination.

decLesEventServer.name: decLesEventServer
decLesEventServer.description: The 'decLesIndex' of the LAN Emulation Server that was involved in this incident. If the value of this object is zero, it indicates that the server no longer exists.

decLesEventServerAtmAddress.name: decLesEventServerAtmAddress

decLesEventClientAtmAddress.description: If known, the ATM address of the LAN Emulation Client that was involved in this incident.

decLesEventClientMacAddress.description: If known, one of the MAC addresses of the client that was involved in this incident. If 'decLesEventReason' is 'duplicateLanDestination' or 'invalidLanDestination', the value of this object will be the MAC address in question.
